{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Chapter Marker for Audiobooks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It adds ID3 Metatag "CHAP=Chapter_Title_by_the_User" by a pop up that asks to the user, the title of each chapter. Then it adds the marker with the correct tag at the mouse position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Key features:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Asks for the title of each chapter by a pop up field\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It can be used very effectively as Armed Action\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It add the prefix "CHAP=" to any title inserted by the user, avoiding sintaxis errors\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab When metadata is used, rendering an MP3, "CHAP=" is automatically added\sa180\par}
}

